5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.lean#L660-L690","name":"EuclideanGeometry.exists_of_range_subset_orthocentricSystem","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.html#EuclideanGeometry.exists_of_range_subset_orthocentricSystem","doc":"This is an auxiliary lemma giving information about the relation\nof two triangles in an orthocentric system; it abstracts some\nreasoning, with no geometric content, that is common to some other\nlemmas.  Suppose the orthocentric system is generated by triangle `t`,\nand we are given three points `p` in the orthocentric system.  Then\neither we can find indices `i₁`, `i₂` and `i₃` for `p` such that `p\ni₁` is the orthocenter of `t` and `p i₂` and `p i₃` are points `j₂`\nand `j₃` of `t`, or `p` has the same points as `t`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.lean#L647-L649","name":"EuclideanGeometry.OrthocentricSystem","kind":"def","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.html#EuclideanGeometry.OrthocentricSystem","doc":"Four points form an orthocentric system if they consist of the\nvertices of a triangle and its orthocenter. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.lean#L623-L631","name":"Affine.Triangle.orthocenter_replace_orthocenter_eq_point","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.html#Affine.Triangle.orthocenter_replace_orthocenter_eq_point","doc":"Suppose we are given a triangle `t₁`, and replace one of its\nvertices by its orthocenter, yielding triangle `t₂` (with vertices not\nnecessarily listed in the same order).  Then the orthocenter of `t₂`\nis the vertex of `t₁` that was replaced. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.lean#L575-L616","name":"Affine.Triangle.altitude_replace_orthocenter_eq_affineSpan","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.html#Affine.Triangle.altitude_replace_orthocenter_eq_affineSpan","doc":"Suppose we are given a triangle `t₁`, and replace one of its\nvertices by its orthocenter, yielding triangle `t₂` (with vertices not\nnecessarily listed in the same order).  Then an altitude of `t₂` from\na vertex that was not replaced is the corresponding side of `t₁`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.lean#L564-L568","name":"Affine.Triangle.affineSpan_orthocenter_point_le_altitude","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.html#Affine.Triangle.affineSpan_orthocenter_point_le_altitude","doc":"The affine span of the orthocenter and a vertex is contained in\nthe altitude. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.lean#L553-L559","name":"Affine.Triangle.dist_orthocenter_reflection_circumcenter_finset","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.html#Affine.Triangle.dist_orthocenter_reflection_circumcenter_finset","doc":"The distance from the orthocenter to the reflection of the\ncircumcenter in a side equals the circumradius, variant using a\n`Finset`. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.lean#L527-L547","name":"Affine.Triangle.dist_orthocenter_reflection_circumcenter","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.html#Affine.Triangle.dist_orthocenter_reflection_circumcenter","doc":"The distance from the orthocenter to the reflection of the\ncircumcenter in a side equals the circumradius. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.lean#L504-L522","name":"Affine.Triangle.eq_orthocenter_of_forall_mem_altitude","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.html#Affine.Triangle.eq_orthocenter_of_forall_mem_altitude","doc":"The orthocenter is the only point lying in any two of the\naltitudes. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.lean#L493-L499","name":"Affine.Triangle.orthocenter_mem_altitude","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.html#Affine.Triangle.orthocenter_mem_altitude","doc":"The orthocenter lies in the altitudes. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.lean#L476-L489","name":"Affine.Triangle.altitude_eq_mongePlane","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.html#Affine.Triangle.altitude_eq_mongePlane","doc":"In the case of a triangle, altitudes are the same thing as Monge\nplanes. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.lean#L469-L471","name":"Affine.Triangle.orthocenter_eq_of_range_eq","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.html#Affine.Triangle.orthocenter_eq_of_range_eq","doc":"Two triangles with the same points have the same orthocenter. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/44c828ca5b12983ef1d4eea5c54f95c2ef52cb36/Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.lean#L463-L465","name":"Affine.Triangle.orthocenter_mem_affineSpan","kind":"theorem","docLink":"./Mathlib/Geometry/Euclidean/MongePoint.html#Affine.Triangle.orthocenter_mem_affineSpan","doc":"The orthocenter lies in the affine span. "},{"sourceLink":"https://github.